IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: COMMUNITY - DIRECTED HEALTHCARE ORGANIZATION THAT PROVIDES QUALITY PRIMARY AND PREVENTIVE CARE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: A COMMUNITY DIRECTED HEALTHCARE ORGANIZATION THAT PROVIDES QUALITY PRIMARY AND PREVENTIVE CARE SERVICES TO THE PEOPLE OF EAST HAWAII. WE ENSURE THAT PATIENT CENTERED, CULTURALLY RESPONSIVE, AND AFFORDABLE HEALTHCARE SERVICES ARE LOCALLY ACCESSIBLE IN OUR COMMUNITIES.
IRS990.Desc: THE BAY CLINIC INC. IS A FEDERALLY QUALIFIED COMMUNITY HEALTH ENTERS SERVING 21,000 ETHNICALLY DIVERSE PATIENTS WITH 58,000 VISITS IN THE DISTRICTS OF HILO, PUNA AND KAU IN EAST AND SOUTH HAWAII ISLAND. IN THE FISCAL YEAR ENDING 2022, THE BAY CLINIC, INC. HAD APPROX 16K+ MEDICAL VISITS, 14K+ DENTAL VISITS, AND 3K+ BH VISITS BETWEEN FACE TO FACE AND VIRTUAL VISITS DURING COVID DECLARATION OF EMERGENCY. BAY CLINIC'S STATE OF THE ART MOBILE HEALTH UNIT CONTINUES ITS DUAL USE, PRIMARY MEDICAL AND DENTAL SERVICES, THE UNIT EXPANDS ACCESS TO COMPREHENSIVE HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO THE MOST REMOTE AND RURAL EAST HAWAII COMMUNITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NON-FIXED PAYMENTS: THE BONUSES ARE DETERMINED BASED ON 3% OF GROSS PAY FOR ALL EMPLOYEES.
LIABILITIES ASSUMED: AS PART OF THE MERGER, WEST HAWAII COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER, INC., ALSO ASSUMED LIABILITIES TOTALING $5,881,994.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: REVIEW OF FORM 990: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY AN ACCOUNTING FIRM BASED ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND INFORMATION PROVIDED BY THE ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT OF THE ORGANIZATION. PRIOR TO FILING, THE CEO AND THE BOARD REVIEWED THE FORM 990.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY: THE CLINIC ESTABLISHED A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY WHICH IS PRESENTED IN THE EMPLOYEE HANDBOOK. ALL EMPLOYEES ARE EXPECTED TO ADHERE TO THIS POLICY. THE ORGANIZATION REVIEWS THIS POLICY WITH NEW HIRES. MANAGEMENT MONITORS EMPLOYEES ON ANY ISSUE THAT MAY INVOLVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST. AN ANNUAL DISCLOSURE FORM IS COMPLETED BY EACH BOARD MEMBER AND MONITORED BY THE BOARD CHAIRPERSON. IF A CONFLICT ARISES, THE ASSOCIATED BOARD PERSON MUST RECUSE THEMSELVES FROM VOTING ON RELATED MATTERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION REVIEW: COMPENSATION FOR THE CEO IS DETERMINED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS BASED ON THE ORGANIZATION'S BUDGET, MARKET DATA FOR THE POSITION, COMPARABLE STUDIES OF SIMILAR ENTITIES, AND THE LOCAL COMPENSATION RATES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DOCUMENT DISCLOSURE: THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
OTHER CHANGES IN NET ASSETS: $ 15,278,165 TRANSFER TO WEST HAWAII COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER INC

STEPS TAKEN TO UNDERGO REQUIRED AUDIT: THE ORGANIZATION FELL BEHIND ON ITS AUDIT COMPLIANCE WITH THEIR PRIOR MANAGEMENT. AS THE MERGER WAS COMPLETED ON JULY 1, 2022, THE CURRENT MANAGEMENT IS ACTIVELY LOOKING FOR AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT TO CONDUCT ITS FINAL AUDIT.
